<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/677070-did-anyone-get-a-sense-of-the-conspiracy">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[did anyone get a sense of the conspiracy theory about the Lindberg baby kidnapping in this book? That Charles was involved? When Anne is taking Charles to Hawaii to die and she wants him to apologize for the affairs and instead he apologizes for "the events of 32" she says "Charles, they caught the man who stole our baby" he replies "no it was me, it was always me". <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
