<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4869211-meredith"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1373380604i/4869211._UX100_CR0,12,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4869211-meredith">Meredith</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I understood it to mean that, particularly in view of his large ego, he felt he was to blame for not having been successful in getting the baby back s<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I understood it to mean that, particularly in view of his large ego, he felt he was to blame for not having been successful in getting the baby back safely. <br /><br />I think this is the way that Benjamin is presenting it as well, because there are no shocked reactions from Anne like there would have been if she understood from his comment that Charles had something to do with the kidnapping. <br /><br />It's the letting her down he's referring to, the failure to be a hero for her. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
